Server:
1)Create a socket- socket()
2)Bind the socket to a port- bind()
3)Read any file sent by client- recvfrom()
4)Send back results to client as desired- sendto()
5)On completion Stop.

Client:
1)Create a socket- socket()
2)Send the desired value to server- sendto()
3)Receive the result- recvfrom()
8)On completion Stop.

In programming, we use the socket library in languages like Python to create UDP sockets.
With socket(socket.AF_INET, socket.SOCK_DGRAM), we can send and receive UDP datagrams between machines,
making it suitable for quick, one-way data communication.
